{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_71","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented FW-M5-002 end-to-end.\n\nThe raw fetch path in [mesh_pipeline.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/mesh_pipeline.py#L104) is now cache-aware and resumable: it validates cached `.ply` and `.swc` files, treats zero-byte/malformed cache entries as invalid, writes fetched assets atomically, supports forced refetch and optional skeleton hard-fail mode, and records structured per-asset provenance with `fetch_status` values like `cache_hit`, `fetched`, `skipped`, and `failed`. The manifest contract in [geometry_contract.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/geometry_contract.py#L111) now stores that `raw_asset_provenance` and can load/merge existing records so rerunning fetches or later processed-asset builds does not clobber prior state.\n\nThe CLI in [02_fetch_meshes.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/scripts/02_fetch_meshes.py#L36) now accepts `--refetch-meshes`, `--refetch-skeletons`, and `--require-skeletons`, writes per-root provenance into the manifest, reports aggregate cache-hit/fetch/failure counts, and preserves existing bundle records on reruns. [03_build_wave_assets.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/scripts/03_build_wave_assets.py#L64) now preserves the raw-fetch provenance when processed assets are built. I also added regression coverage in [tests/test_mesh_pipeline_fetch.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_mesh_pipeline_fetch.py#L44), plus manifest/integration assertions in [tests/test_geometry_contract.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_geometry_contract.py#L52) and [tests/test_config_paths.py](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/tests/test_config_paths.py#L72). Config examples were updated with the new knobs in [config/local.yaml](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/config/local.yaml) and [config/visual_subset.example.yaml](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/config/visual_subset.example.yaml).\n\nVerified with `make test` and `.venv/bin/python -m unittest tests.test_mesh_pipeline_fetch -v`. Both passed."}}
